{"word":"κύβηβος","slug":"κύβηβος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n60509\" key=\"ku/bhbos\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">κύβηβος</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ον</itype>, (<etym lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"etym\">κύβη</etym>) <sense id=\"n60509.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">stooping with the head,</tr_> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ EM\">EM</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">543.10</biblScope></bibl>. </sense> <sense n=\"II\" id=\"n60509.1\" level=\"2\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">Κύβηβος</orth> [<foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ῠ], <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ὁ</gen></foreign>, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">minister of Cybele</tr_>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0260.tlg001:36\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Semon.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">36</biblScope> </bibl>; cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">κυβέβις· γάλλος, κτλ</foreign>., <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hsch.\">Hsch.</a></author> </bibl>: generally, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">one ecstatic</tr_> or <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">frantic</tr_>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0434.tlg001:82\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Cratin.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">82</biblScope> </bibl>:—hence <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">κῠβηβάω</orth>, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">to be frantic</tr_>, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Phot.</author></bibl>, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hsch.\">Hsch.</a></author></bibl>, cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg4099.tlg001:543:11\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ EM\">EM</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">543.11</biblScope> </bibl> (-<itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">βειν</itype> codd.):— <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hsch.\">Hsch.</a></author> </bibl> also has the forms <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">Κυβήκη</orth> (<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0233.tlg001:120\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Hippon.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">120</biblScope> </bibl>) and <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">Κύβηκος</orth>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}